  "texts": [
    "Many of the technologies that youth create and engage with are built around wearable sensing (through the micro:bit), computer vision (through Scratch), and other low-cost technologies that are modeled after professional/commercial sports technologies.",
    "More than 3000 youth and hundreds of educators/facilitators have contributed to and participated in the activities.",
    "Our research team is inspired by design-based research, and uses a mixed methods approach to design, implement, and study our various implementations of learning experiences that engage youth in talking about and creating novel sports technologies using AI/ML.",
    "Broadly speaking, our work across contexts has encouraged us to think about the unique affordances and expectations of each of the different contexts.",
    "We find that the spaces require different approaches in terms of tools, ethics, learning, teaching, and assessment."
  ],
